fires that occurred at almost the same time last week in two buildings on opposite sides of a street have been determined to have been deliberately set according to the police one fire in a house that had been subdivided into apartments and was owned by wesleyan university was started with gasoline or some other accelerant the police said wesleyan teachers and staff members living in the building escaped from the fire in the predawn hours of april 27 without injury less than an hour later the second fire broke out in a garage across the street the police said that they had also linked that fire to some form of accelerant but that they had not definitively concluded that the two fires were connected

